{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_28","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-api-incubator:1.58.0-alpha`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5785-fails-javac-compile-io.opentelemetry-opentelemetry-api-incubator-1.58.0-alpha-5fd3f98c\n\nThe underlying incompatibility was a `javac` failure against a removed API: the first Gradle run failed in `compileTestJava` because `io.opentelemetry.api.incubator.config.GlobalConfigProvider` could not be resolved in `tests/src/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-api-incubator/1.58.0-alpha/src/test/java/io_opentelemetry/opentelemetry_api_incubator/Opentelemetry_api_incubatorTest.java` (`human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-api-incubator:1.58.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T13-56-52-308558Z.log`).\n\nHowever, the most likely stage that actually failed the automation was artifact capture/preservation after the compile fix. The generation session log records a concrete fix: remove `GlobalConfigProvider` import/usages, rework the config-provider test around `ConfigProvider.noop()` / `DeclarativeConfigException`, and update `ExtendedOpenTelemetry` assertions to expect `DeclarativeConfigProperties.empty()` (`human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-api-incubator:1.58.0-alpha/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T13-58-18-881726Z.log`). After that, the next three Gradle reruns all ended with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` (`human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-api-incubator:1.58.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T13-58-18-899737Z.log`, `.../gradle-test-2026-05-04T14-00-12-606607Z.log`, `.../gradle-test-2026-05-04T14-00-52-722900Z.log`).\n\nDespite those successful reruns, `stats/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-api-incubator/1.58.0-alpha/execution-metrics.json` still reports `status: failure`, `ending_commit` equal to `starting_commit` (`93b0ad21d411361562a52d7289bda44dc58527d9`), `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None`. The preserved commit on the branch (`8a00306092`, “Preserve failed automation work for issue #5785”) also deletes `tests/src/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-api-incubator/1.58.0-alpha/**`, so the branch keeps logs but not the adapted test sources. Dynamic-access coverage was not produced.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-api-incubator:1.58.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T13-56-52-308558Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-api-incubator:1.58.0-alpha/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T13-58-18-881726Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-api-incubator:1.58.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T13-58-18-899737Z.log`\n- `stats/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-api-incubator/1.58.0-alpha/execution-metrics.json`\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Restore the `tests/src/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-api-incubator/1.58.0-alpha/` project from commit `93b0ad21d4` (or regenerate it), then reapply the edits described in `pi-generation-2026-05-04T13-58-18-881726Z.log`.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-api-incubator:1.58.0-alpha` to confirm the recovered test still passes.\n3. If green, commit the restored test files and refresh the run metrics/artifacts, since the preserved branch currently contains only logs plus deletion of the generated test scaffold."}}
